Create a Waterfall Chart
Use a waterfall chart to show the cumulative effect of sequentially introduced positive or negative values with breakdowns of value totals.
In the lens, click  and then select the Waterfall chart type.
In the X-Axis field, add the dimension to analyze the measures by.
In the Y-Axis field, add the measure, such as the sum of amount.
To change the chart display, click  and set the chart properties in the Formatting panel.
